As part of its 10th anniversary, a leading player in real estate, Adron Homes and Properties, has unveiled its  Health Festival. The company said the programme is aimed at giving back to the public for the goodwill it has enjoyed over the years. Its Director-General (DG) of Sales and Marketing, Mrs Folashade Oloruntoba, said yesterday  in Lagos: “Adron Homes and Properties is poised to extend her hands of gratitude to the public for the support we have continued to enjoy over the years, and the confidence the public has reposed in us as their first choice in housing solution.   Dana Air laments short stay off the skies     Stakeholder seeks end to multiple taxation in ports     NBC’s investment crosses 1 billion euros   ”Adron Homes thought it wise to extend health care to the nooks and crannies of the country, understanding the importance of health, because as the great wise saying goes, Health is wealth. We have decided to host a mega health outreach tagged Adron Health Festival.” ”The public will have access to basic health checks and services at the event since we firmly believe that investing in one’s health means investing in one’s future. The DG added: “We are urging the public to take advantage of this opportunity to obtain free health care, as we will be easily accessible in numerous sites around the country, including Brent Mall, Apata Ibadan, and Jericho Mall, Oyo State.’’ Others are Ifo Market Sagamu in Ogun State. The Sabo Market Sagamu will host the programme in Osun State. Lagos locations include Agege Market, Idumota Market, and Ojodu Berger at the Oando gas station, and Ketu roundabout while UTC Market, Area 10, and Maraba Market are the places to go in Abuja.